Living project-status document, not source code — governs what an editor should believe is currently true about the system's architecture and open work, distinct from `SPEC.md` (frozen design), `UNIMPLEMENTED.md` (backlog), and `DECISIONS.md` (rationale log). Must be updated whenever active focus shifts; treat its "last updated" date and "Done/Open" split as the authoritative snapshot over any stale impression from other docs or older ADRs.

Key facts an editor needs before touching this repo: agents use native Read/Edit tools directly, not a custom access layer — `ctx-context <path>` (renamed from `ctx-access`) serves rollup+intent chains read-only and is injected automatically via a `PostToolUse` hook in `.claude/settings.json` on every Read/Grep/Glob, fail-open and deduplicated per session. Freshness of `.context/` is tracked by content hashes in `.context/<dir>/hashes.json`; regeneration is a separate post-session step (`ctx-scan <dir> --update`), not automatic — the Stop hook only reports staleness. `ctx-verify` is the single CI checkpoint (format+build+lint+test+unused-deps via cargo-machete); the old parallel `ci.sh`/`template/.github` stack is retired, so don't expect duplicate CI paths. The sandbox (`ctx-cage`) is safety-only now — RW workspace, masked secrets as empty files, offline except a passthrough proxy for egress, subscription-based auth — with the old broker/protocol/client architecture deleted (ADR-035..043 cover this pivot in detail).

Currently open work: no billed headless `ctx-run` has succeeded yet (proxy/TLS/OAuth path untested end-to-end); this repo's own `.context/` tree is stale (pre-pivot content, describes the deleted broker architecture) and needs `ctx-scan . --update --approve` to reseed (~110 leaves, billed, not yet run) — so don't trust `.context/` output for this repo below the root level. A Phase 5 e2e smoke fixture (stub and billed modes) is planned but not built. Several things are deliberately deferred and documented as such, not bugs: no seccomp filter (namespaces+no_new_privs+offline suffice for now), OAuth refresh mid-session isn't handled (single-host proxy limitation), orphaned `.context` directory subtrees aren't auto-pruned. Verification commands: `ctx-verify [crate]`, `ctx-cage <dir> --self-test stub`, `ctx-context <path>`, `ctx-scan <dir> --check`.